Foot & mouth disease - UK (39) 20010405.0680
[1
Date: Fri 6 April, 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Ministry of Agriculture Fisheries and Food website [edited
<http://www.maff.gov.uk/animalh/diseases/fmd/default.htm>
<http://www.maff.gov.uk/animalh/diseases/fmd/sitrep.PDF>

Figures as of 19:00 Thu 5 April 2001
---------------------------------------------
1057 confirmed cases (33 new cases in the period 19:00 4 April to 19:00 5
April).
Update 09:00 Friday 6 April:
A further 4 cases have been confirmed. The total number of confirmed cases
now stands at 1061 (breakdown of new cases by county). Details of
individual cases are also added to the list of infected premises at the
time they become available.
Slaughter/disposal numbers at 19:00 Thu 5 April 2001:
Total number animals slaughtered or identified as being for slaughter is
around 1 204 000.
Number of animals slaughtered 764 000.
Number of animals destroyed 498 000.
Summary Map, 31 Mar 2001 (for some reason this map is not being updated):
<http://www.maff.gov.uk/animalh/diseases/fmd/maps/overview.htm>
But statistics also available at:
<http://www.hjones.plus.com/graph.htm>
